author: Chun-Nan Hsu and Hilmar Schuschel and Ya-Ting Yang
title: The ANNIGMA-Wrapper Approach to Neural Nets Feature Selection for Knowledge Discovery and Data Mining
window: concentrated on distinguishing the presence of heart disease (value 1,2 3,4 in the classification) from absence (value 0). Missing values in both databases are all replaced by zero. Ionosphere This dataset has 351 records of 34 features. The goal is to classify two types of radar returns from the ionosphere. ``Good'' radar returns are those showing evidence of some type of structure in the ionosphere.
